<HEAD>Honolulu Get Christmas Serenade On Radio</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Beachgoers soaking up the Hawaiian summer sun were serenaded by the strains of `` White Christmas'' and `` Jingle Bell Rock'' on a radio station here. <ORGANIZATION> KSSK </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> billed Wednesday as a day of yuletide music to remind listeners that drinking and driving kills. `` We've had 41 traffic fatalities so far this year and if we continue at this rate we'll have 46 more before Christmas,'' said <PERSON> Suzi </PERSON> <PERSON> Mechler </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> KSSK </ORGANIZATION> director of operations. `` So we're playing them their Christmas music now.'' There were 32 traffic fatalities on <LOCATION> Honolulu </LOCATION> roads at the same time last year, police said. <PERSON> Mechler </PERSON> said the music also was played to give would-be drinken drivers a desire to live until Christmas and to think before getting behind the wheel. <PERSON> Mechler </PERSON> said the station has celebrated Christmas in June for the past three or four years.
