 Flamboyant pop singer will <PERSON> Cyndi </PERSON> <PERSON> Lauper </PERSON> will sing the praise of education next week when she receives a belated high school diploma. <PERSON> Lauper </PERSON> will get her sheepskin along with the 400 graduates of <ORGANIZATION> Richmond </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Queens </LOCATION> at Monday's ceremonies, school officials said Wednesday. <PERSON> Lauper </PERSON>, whose hits include `` Girls Just Wan na Have Fun'' and `` True Colors,'' dropped out of the high school several years ago, said her publicist, <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Riggs </PERSON>. After getting her diploma, <PERSON> Lauper </PERSON> will address the class on the importance of education, <PERSON> Riggs </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Lauper </PERSON> already has a high-school equivalency diploma.
