<DATELINE>LENOX, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Friends of conductor <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> <PERSON> Bernstein </PERSON> have orchestrated a birthday bash to include appearances by <PERSON> Beverly </PERSON> <PERSON> Sills </PERSON>, <PERSON> Lauren </PERSON> <PERSON> Bacall </PERSON>, <PERSON> Betty </PERSON> <PERSON> Comden </PERSON> and <PERSON> Phyllis </PERSON> <PERSON> Newman </PERSON>. The <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> <PERSON> Bernstein </PERSON> Gala Birthday Performance is a benefit concert set for the composer's 70th birthday, Aug. 25, to raise money for the <ORGANIZATION> Berkshire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Music </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Tanglewood </LOCATION>, where <PERSON> Bernstein </PERSON> got his conducting start. Miss <PERSON> Sills </PERSON> will be host of the event that will include performances by the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Symphony </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Orchestra </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pops </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Orchestra </ORGANIZATION> and the Tanglewood Festival Chorus. The concert plans to celebrate <PERSON> Bernstein </PERSON>'s accomplishments in popular music with excerpts from his `` West Side Story,'' `` On the Town'' and others.
