74 erupted last October when the government declared invalid much of the currency in circulation and offered no compensation. On March 18, several days of student unrest climaxed in a rampage by students and others that was swiftly crushed by police and military units. A government panel announced only two deaths and said 625 people were arrested, many of them since freed. But diplomatic sources told reporters in <LOCATION> Bangkok </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Thailand </LOCATION>, that as many as 100 people died in the March violence.
