e has been relieved of his command. During the hearings, a pathologist testified <PERSON> Mirecki </PERSON> died of `` sheer terror.'' The recruit's phobia of being dragged under water triggered heart failure that was followed by drowning, the pathologist said. <PERSON> Mirecki </PERSON> panicked during an exercise known as `` sharks and daisies'' in which instructors grabbed students in head-holds to simulate a panicking air crash survivor. The exercise now has students practice rescue exercises on each other rather than instructors. The school was closed March 29 and reopened Monday with instructors barred from touching trainees. Students also are required to immediately be pulled from training if they say they want to quit or show fear, panic or excessive fatigue.
