<DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Residents of this small mining town dread the end of a truce that gave them nearly three months of relative peace from fighting between U.S.-backed rebels and leftist Sandinista government troops. Both sides have sympathizers here, but everyone `` fears the return of the fighters,'' said <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Toledo </PERSON>, owner of a small food shop. <PERSON> Santo </PERSON> <PERSON> Domingo </PERSON> nestles between two hills in the central Chontales province, a region which has seen intense fighting during the 6 -LCB- - year-old war between the rebels, known as Contras, and the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION> Military sources say the violence has steadily diminished since a cease-fire began March 23. The town's only ambulance, once busy transporting war wounded, now ferries sick children to the local health center. Residents like <PERSON> Eudoro </PERSON> <PERSON> Castro </PERSON>, 43, are now left more or less in peace. <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> explained how he's gotten by in a war that has killed 26,500 people, wounded another 25,000 and nearly destroyed the Nicaraguan economy. `` The Contras come along and demand a cow. I give it to them,'' <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> said. `` The Sandinistas come by, I give them one too. I'm happy they are leaving me in peace now to work. Military sources admit there have been some abuses by Sandinista soldiers, abuses that have helped the Contras build a strong base of popular support in the region. The fatigue-clad soldiers are still here, but now they doze on the shaded sidewalks instead of preparing for another round of combat. This region is also headquarters for a Contra force of about 2,000 rebels. Military sources who asked not to be identified said the army has been in contact with various rebel factions during the cease-fire, attempting to persuade them to lay down their arms. The army has had little success, the sources said. The truce is due to expire at the end of June. The last round of