military issues for The congressman is one of five <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> members of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> whose names have come up in the case. Ms. <PERSON> Galvin </PERSON> remains on <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>'s staff as a legislative assistant dealing with other issues. Ms. <PERSON> Galvin </PERSON> was reassigned because she and <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> agreed she would be in an `` untenable position'' if she continued to handle military matters because her father, defense consultant <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Galvin </PERSON>, `` is a principal in the investigation,'' said a spokesman for <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Doug </PERSON> <PERSON> Hattaway </PERSON>. <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> and the other four congressmen reported under scrutiny have all said they are not targets of the inquiry. The others are Reps. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Chappell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Fla </LOCATION>., chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Appropriations defense subcommittee; <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Downey </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stratton </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> procurement subcommittee; and <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Dyson </PERSON>, D-Md., a member of <PERSON> Stratton </PERSON> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> is also on the <LOCATION> Stratton </LOCATION> panel. <PERSON> Weinberger </PERSON>, one of President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s closest friends and staunchest allies, complained that the case was prompting <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and the public to lose sight of the continuing need for a strong defense. `` You do n't close a bank because there's been a bank robbery,'' <PERSON> Weinberger </PERSON> said. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Pent