<HEAD>Production Falls This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 241,988 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's 255,207, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, in which 221,924 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 161,760 cars this week, compared with 168,088 a week ago and 148,651 in the same week in 1987. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 80,228, compared with last week's 87,119 and last year's 73,273. Canadian automakers were to build 24,310 cars this week, down from 24,730 a week ago and up from last year's 17,455. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,440, compared with 20,497 a week ago and 19,154 in the same week last year.
