f. <PERSON> Deo </PERSON> in a ruling last week refused to dissociate himself from the case, saying there were no legal grounds for the request. The contempt of court application Thursday said that <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Carbide </ORGANIZATION>'s request was a direct attack on <PERSON> Deo </PERSON> and an attempt to intimidate him. It was designed to obstruct the course of justice, the petition said.
